inline_comments.message:
There  are two problems.  1) The variable badparms is supposed to be a list of bad parameters.  You are not creating a list with tempBadParms.  You are assigning single values to it. 2) You never assign tempBadParms (which I assume you meant to be a list) back to badparams.  badparams is a string that is passed in by the parent method and when you are done updating it, the badparams is utilized in a log and exception message at the parent/calling level.

I think your assignment statements should have been:
tempBadParams = tempBadParams.concat("whatever the param");

Then at the bottom: 
badparams = badparams.concat(tempBadParams);

But, this is all more complicated than the original code.
